<paragraph blockId="50.[151,1436,152,1970]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,274,1421,1447]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Notes.</emphasis>
In the original description Benhauer (1934) stated that he had a unique specimen of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bernhauer" authorityYear="1934" box="[1284,1428,1421,1446]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Philonthus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ruficauda">
<emphasis box="[1284,1428,1421,1446]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">P. ruficauda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The specimen mentioned above agrees with the original description by 
<bibRefCitation author="Bernhauer, M." box="[993,1204,1458,1484]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" pagination="112 - 119" refId="ref48007" refString="Bernhauer, M. (1934) Neue Staphyliniden aus Argentinien (Col.) (34. Beitrag zur Kenntnis der sudamerikanischen Fauna). Revista de Entomologia, 4, 112 - 119 (III)." type="journal article" year="1934">Bernhauer (1934)</bibRefCitation>
, being the 
<typeStatus box="[1334,1436,1458,1484]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">holotype</typeStatus>
fixed by monotypy (
<bibRefCitation author="ICZN" box="[389,528,1496,1522]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" refId="ref50424" refString="ICZN (1999) International Code of Zoological Nomenclatur e. Fourth Edition. The International Trust for Zoological Nomenclature, London, xxix + 306 pp." type="book" year="1999">ICZN 1999</bibRefCitation>
, Article 73.1.2).
</paragraph>
